Wire wheeling and/or sandblasting unfort. doesn't remove all rust either.
Rust will remain in the pores of the steel, and the acid washes/zinc
chromate treatments help kill/prevent that until you get the primer and
finish on.

David, your bus looks absolutely beautiful. The combination of the tedious
labor of the wire wheels, I believe, was the way to go. I plan on similar,
followed by the acid mostly for flushing the rails where I can't get it.

Is that grey DP? or a painted finish over a primer?

Well see you all in 100.....

